now ate good.\nThree varieties: Sun-Maid Seeded\n(seeds removed); Sun-Maid Seedless\n(grown without seeds); Sun-Maid\nClusters (on the stem). All dealers\nsell them. Insist upon the Sun-Maid\nbrand.\nSend for free book, \"Sun-Maid Rec\nipes,\" describing many ways to serve.\nCALIFORNIA ASSOCIATED RAISIN CO, FRESNO, CALIFORNIA\nMembership 10,000 Growers\nCut This Out and Send It S\nCalifornia Associated Raisin Co. a\nDept. N-SS, Frfaoo, CaL\nPlease send me foot book, \"Sun-Maid\nRecipes,\" free.\nAddress\nChy\n~..s\nT\nElectrolytic Copper\nTouches New Level;\nSells at 12.25c lb.\ni\nNew York, March 9.\u2014Sales of elec\ntrolytic copper were reported in small\nlots at 12:25 Wednesday, the lowest\nprice touched since 1916. Notwith\nstanding the recent decrease in pro\nduction, stocks are said to be accumu\nlating and very few buyers were re\nported in the market taken at the low\nprices. The larger producing interests\nhave not met the decline, but their\nquotations of 12% to 13 cents are\nnominal.\n15.00 CASH\u2014$2.50 WEEKLY\nWILL DELIVER A\nMONARCH RANGE\nTO YOUR HOME\nWith a Monarch you will have juicy roasts, perfect\nbread, and crisp pie crusts. These are every day\noccurrences with folks who use a Monarch.\nAsk your neighbor, she knows.\nMore Monarchs sold in Montana than any other\nrange.\n\"It's Malleable\"\nYOUR CREDIT IS GOOD\nSTANDARD FURNITURE CO.\n412-414 First Avenue South\n\u0152fje #a&e\n&pectaltp\n&Jjop\n417 Central\nDemi Linen Initial\nHandkerchiefs\nS ffoir $11\nTODAY ONLY","height":"23064","width":"19512"}}
